header.gameNote: HORIZON LEAGUE MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - SEMIFINAL AT VALPARAISO IN

article.headline: Detroit 63, Cleveland St. 58
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Ray McCallum scored 26 points and Detroit avenged a pair of losses to Cleveland State during the regular season with a 63-58 victory over the Vikings on Saturday in the semifinals of the Horizon League tournament. The third-seeded Titans (21-13) advance to the championship game Tuesday at top-seeded Valparaiso, which beat fifth-seeded Butler 65-46 Saturday night. Detroit used a 14-2 run to build a 47-35 lead with 12:03 remaining, only to see second-seeded Cleveland State (22-10) answer with its own 14-2 run to tie it at 49-all with 3:07 left. The Titans went up by four on a fast-break dunk by Chase Simon and a pair of free throws from McCallum, and hit 8 of 10 free throws in the final minute to hold off the Vikings. D'Aundray Brown had 17 points for Cleveland State, which had swept Detroit in the regular season, including a 77-64 victory 10 days ago.
